<L N="75">More vnto him al &thorn;us said he:<NOTE PLACE="foot">Vnto him &thorn;us answerd he.</NOTE></L>
<L>"Peter, for suth I say to &thorn;e,</L>
<L>In &thorn;is werld &thorn;ou es &thorn;e stone<NOTE PLACE="foot">world.</NOTE></L>
<L>&THORN;at I sal big my kirk opone" &mdash;<NOTE PLACE="foot">sall. opon.</NOTE></L>
<L>&THORN;at menes &thorn;us: I sal mak &thorn;e<NOTE PLACE="foot">&thorn;at es to say I sall.</NOTE></L>
<L N="80">&THORN;e heuyd of hali kirk to be:<NOTE PLACE="foot">&thorn;e fehlt.</NOTE></L>
<L>For Peter es noght els to mene</L>
<L>Bot a stone &thorn;at in erth es clene;<NOTE PLACE="foot">stane. sene st. clene.</NOTE>
<PB REF="00000202.tif" N="64"></L>
<L>And for his (name) of stone es grayd,<NOTE PLACE="foot1">Ms. hie st. his, name fehlt.</NOTE><NOTE PLACE="foot2">And sen his name &thorn;arof was tone,</NOTE></L>
<L>&THORN;ar-fore oure lord &thorn;us to him said:<NOTE PLACE="foot2">&THORN;arfore said our lord allone.</NOTE></L>
<L N="85">&THORN;at stone to my will sall I wirk<NOTE PLACE="foot2">stane.</NOTE></L>
<L>And ground &thorn;aron all hali kirk.</L>
<L>And more &yogh;it vnto him he hight:<NOTE PLACE="foot2">And ouer said Jhesus alweldand</NOTE></L>
<L>"&THORN;e &yogh;ates of hell sal haf no might,<NOTE PLACE="foot2">&THORN;at &thorn;e &yogh;ates of hell sal noght withstand.</NOTE></L>
<L>Ogaynes &thorn;at stone when it wil strike:<NOTE PLACE="foot2">Ogains. stane. will.</NOTE></L>
<L N="90">Of might &amp; strenkith sal it be slike".</L>
<L>And vnto Peter &yogh;it &thorn;us said he:<NOTE PLACE="foot2">&thorn;an st. &yogh;it &thorn;us.</NOTE></L>
<L>"&THORN;e kays of heuyn sall I gif &thorn;e".<NOTE PLACE="foot2">kaies. sal.</NOTE><NOTE PLACE="foot2">Aw.</NOTE></L>
<L>And &thorn;is Peter, &thorn;at was Andrew bro&thorn;er,<NOTE PLACE="foot2">And &thorn;is ilk Peter, Andrews b.</NOTE></L>
<L>Awe ful right bifor al o&thorn;er</L>
<L N="95">Forto kepe &thorn;e kays of heuyn,<NOTE PLACE="foot2">haue. kayes.</NOTE></L>
<L>Sen he was first to graunt bi steuyn.<NOTE PLACE="foot2">Sen &thorn;at he first granted bi st.</NOTE></L>
<L>&THORN;e right trouth in hert to haue,</L>
<L>Whith-outen whilk none may be saue:<NOTE PLACE="foot1">Ms. whith st. with.</NOTE><NOTE PLACE="foot2">Withowten whill (!) nane sal.</NOTE></L>
<L>For none mai entre at heuyn &yogh;ate<NOTE PLACE="foot2">Ne none. enter.</NOTE></L>
<L N="100">Bot &thorn;ai be trew in trouth algate.<NOTE PLACE="foot2">Bot if &thorn;ai trow trewly a.</NOTE></L>
<L>And &thorn;arfore best wurthi es he<NOTE PLACE="foot2">wor&thorn;i.</NOTE></L>
<L>To kepe &thorn;e kays of &thorn;at entre,<NOTE PLACE="foot2">kayes.</NOTE></L>
<L>To gif &thorn;am frely entre &thorn;are<NOTE PLACE="foot2">So &thorn;at al &thorn;a sal entir &thorn;are.</NOTE></L>
<L>&THORN;at trewly trous, als he did are,<NOTE PLACE="foot2">trowes. (he fehlt).</NOTE></L>
<L N="105">Howe Jhesus Crist es goddes sun<NOTE PLACE="foot2">&thorn;at st. howe.</NOTE></L>
<L>And kome into &thorn;is werld to wun<NOTE PLACE="foot2">come in &thorn;is. forto won.</NOTE></L>
<L>And of Mari tuke fless and blude<NOTE PLACE="foot2">toke. blode.</NOTE></L>
<L>And for man-kinde was done on rude.<NOTE PLACE="foot2">died on &thorn;e rode.</NOTE></L>
<L>By kays of heuyn vnderstand we here<NOTE PLACE="foot2">heuyn (kayes?).</NOTE></L>
<L N="110">No-thing bot might &amp; playn powere,</L>
<L>&THORN;at god gaf vnto Peter &thorn;are.</L>
<L>For on &thorn;is maner said he mare:<NOTE PLACE="foot2">Das lat. Citat fehlt.</NOTE></L></LG>
<Q>Quodcumque ligaueris super terram. &mdash;</Q>
<LG>
<L>"Al &thorn;at &thorn;ou bindes in erth, saide he,<NOTE PLACE="foot2">All.</NOTE></L>
<L>In heuyn sall &thorn;ai bunden be;<NOTE PLACE="foot2">&thorn;ai sal.</NOTE></L>
<L N="115">And in erth wham &thorn;ou leses euyn,<NOTE PLACE="foot2">109&mdash;115) Die Versenden sind nicht sichtbar (Anfang der 2. Col.)</NOTE><NOTE PLACE="foot2">And &thorn;at in erth . . lesed of the,</NOTE></L>
<L>&THORN;ai sall be lesid in blis of heuyn" &mdash;<NOTE PLACE="foot2">In heuyn sal he (le)sed be.</NOTE></L>
<L>&THORN;at menes what &thorn;ou in erth wil do,<NOTE PLACE="foot2">&thorn;at es to say what &thorn;ou will do,</NOTE></L>
<L>In heuyn sall I assent &thorn;arto.<NOTE PLACE="foot2">My seluen sall assent &thorn;arto.</NOTE></L>
<L>&THORN;us gaf he to Peter, als we fynd,<NOTE PLACE="foot2">to fehlt.</NOTE></L>
<L N="120">Ful power forto lese and bynd &mdash;<NOTE PLACE="foot2">ful fehlt.</NOTE></L>
<L>And noght so vnto hym allane,<NOTE PLACE="foot2">Bot noght euinly to.</NOTE></L>
<L>Bot als to appostels euerilkane;<NOTE PLACE="foot2">als fehlt. to &thorn;e.</NOTE></L>
<L>And sethin es graunted &thorn;at same state<NOTE PLACE="foot2">he granted &thorn;at ilk st.</NOTE></L>
<L>Vnto ilk preste and ilk prelate<NOTE PLACE="foot2">To ilka prest.</NOTE></L>
<L N="125">&THORN;at cure has here of cristen men,</L>
<L>&THORN;e ways of Crist &thorn;am forto ken. &mdash;<NOTE PLACE="foot2">Cristes wayes.</NOTE></L>
<L>How Peter went in Cristes way,<NOTE PLACE="foot2">And how he w.</NOTE></L>
<L>Leris vs &thorn;e legend of &thorn;is day,<NOTE PLACE="foot2">Schewes &thorn;e seruys of his day.</NOTE></L>
<L>Of saynt Peter and saynt Paul in-fere<NOTE PLACE="foot2">Sen s. P.</NOTE></L>
<L N="130">Es on one day in ilk a &yogh;ere.<NOTE PLACE="foot2">Er rede on a day in &thorn;e &yogh;ere.</NOTE></L>
<L>And what dedis on &thorn;at day war done,<NOTE PLACE="foot2">And fehlt. dedes. was.</NOTE></L>
<L>Who will tak hede, mai here alsone.<NOTE PLACE="foot2">Herkins and &yogh;e sal here sone.</NOTE></L>
</LG>
