<DIV3 TYPE="section">
<HEAD>De passione s. Petri.</HEAD>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>In &thorn;e thrid &yogh;ere forto neuyn</L>
<L>Efter &thorn;at Criste was hent to heuyn,<NOTE PLACE="foot2">Crist.</NOTE></L>
<L N="135">Saynt Peter als bisschop held his see<NOTE PLACE="foot2">S. P. &thorn;an bissch(op) . .</NOTE></L>
<L>In Anthioche, a ful riche cete.<NOTE PLACE="foot2">Of Antioche . .</NOTE></L>
<L>And in &thorn;at lordschip gun he lend<NOTE PLACE="foot2">And &thorn;are . . lend</NOTE>
<PB REF="00000203.tif" N="65"></L>
<L>To seuyn &yogh;eres war fully end.<NOTE PLACE="foot2">. . till end.</NOTE></L>
<L>And se&thorn;in he went obout precheand</L>
<L N="140">Two &yogh;eres thurgh in diuers land.</L>
<L>When two &yogh;eres war past al playne,<NOTE PLACE="foot2">And when. .</NOTE></L>
<L>&THORN;an vnto Rome he come ogayne.</L>
<L>He made &thorn;ore bisschops of &thorn;e law</L>
<L>And lered &thorn;am lely Crist to knaw;<NOTE PLACE="foot2">And kend. .</NOTE></L>
<L N="145">To preche &thorn;e pople neuer he sesid,<NOTE PLACE="foot2">Of preching. .</NOTE></L>
<L>And Cristes law so fast encresid.</L>
<L>&THORN;an had &thorn;e fende ful grete enuy,</L>
<L>For &thorn;e folk forsoke al maumetry<NOTE PLACE="foot2">&thorn;e fehlt.</NOTE></L>
<L>And trowed in Crist, als &thorn;ai war kend:</L>
<L N="150">&THORN;arfore a fals disciple he send,</L>
<L>To ger &thorn;e folk trow in &thorn;e fende</L>
<L>And so with syn &thorn;aire sawles to schende.</L>
<L>His name was cald Simon Magus,</L>
<L>And sum of his wirking was &thorn;us:</L>
<L N="155">With deuils craft he kouth him dight</L>
<L>Forto seme ane angell bright.<NOTE PLACE="foot2">At seme (die andern Anf&auml;nge wie in Harl.).</NOTE><NOTE PLACE="foot2">133&mdash;156 Nur Versanf&auml;nge sind erhalten.</NOTE></L>
<L>Simon Magus slike wunders wroght:<NOTE PLACE="foot2">Vor 157 stand eine lat. Ueberschrift (Quare Magum dicunt?).</NOTE><NOTE PLACE="foot2">wonders.</NOTE></L>
<L>In grete errure &thorn;e folk he broght:</L>
<L>He gert &thorn;am trow, whore he wold wun,<NOTE PLACE="foot2">wald won.</NOTE></L>
<L N="160">&THORN;at he was Crist and goddes sun;</L>
<L>He scheude &thorn;am many wunder thing:</L>
<L>He gert images &amp; hundes syng,<NOTE PLACE="foot2">. . (ima)ges speke and hundes sing.</NOTE></L>
<L>Nedders made he quik of bras,</L>
<L>In diuers schap oft-sithes he was.</L>
<L N="165">Als Crist here his disciples send<NOTE PLACE="foot2">desciples sent</NOTE></L>
<L>To teche &thorn;e folk &thorn;aire mis to mend,<NOTE PLACE="foot2">. . &thorn;e men f(or) amendment.</NOTE></L>
<L>So sent he his disciples sere<NOTE PLACE="foot2">desyples.</NOTE></L>
<L>Of fendes lare &thorn;e folk to lere;<NOTE PLACE="foot2">to folk at lere.</NOTE></L>
<L>And mony &thorn;aire lare vnderstode<NOTE PLACE="foot2">many.</NOTE></L>
<L N="170">And held &thorn;am goddes ful trew &amp; gode.<NOTE PLACE="foot2">(And) honord &thorn;am with main and mode.</NOTE></L>
<L>When Symon Magus herd folk tell<NOTE PLACE="foot2">(When) &thorn;is fend Simond herd tell.</NOTE></L>
<L>In Anthioche how it bifell,</L>
<L>How &thorn;at saint Peter had bene &thorn;are</L>
<L>And turned &thorn;e folk to goddes lare:</L>
<L N="175">&THORN;eder he hasted him in hy,</L>
<L>To turne &thorn;am vnto maumetry<NOTE PLACE="foot2">. . turned.</NOTE></L>
<L>With mony meruayles &thorn;at he did.<NOTE PLACE="foot2">(With) fals miracles &thorn;at he dyd.</NOTE></L>
<L>And when his dede was knawen &amp; kid</L>
<L>Vnto saynt Peter whore he was,<NOTE PLACE="foot2">whare. Die lesbaren W&ouml;rter der folg. Verse stimmen mit Harl. &uuml;berein.</NOTE></L>
<L N="180">Grete sorow in his hert he has:</L>
<L>To Antioche ogayn he went</L>
<L>And vnto Criste turned &thorn;aire entent;</L>
<L>He broght &thorn;am to right trouth ogayn</L>
<L>And saued &thorn;aire sawles fro endles payn.</L>
<L N="185">Simon Magus and his men&yogh;e</L>
<L>Went &thorn;an to Jerusalem &thorn;e cete</L>
<L>And &thorn;ore thurgh falshede of his saw<NOTE PLACE="foot1">Ms. &amp; st. of.</NOTE><NOTE PLACE="foot2">falshed of.</NOTE></L>
<L>He turned &thorn;e folk to trow his law.</L>
<L>Saint Peter &thorn;an sone &thorn;eder &yogh;ede</L>
<L N="190">And prechid ogayns his falshede;</L>
<L>&THORN;at Simon techid &thorn;e folk vnto,</L>
<L>Saint Peter said it was noght so.</L>
<L>So &thorn;at &thorn;e puple was in were</L>
<L>Whethir of &thorn;ir laws &thorn;at &thorn;ai suld lere.</L>
<L N="195">&THORN;an &thorn;e moste maysters of &thorn;e toun</L>
<L>Ordand ane congregacioune,</L>
<L>By &thorn;aire sinagoges to aspy</L>
<L>Whe&thorn;ir of &thorn;am suld haf maystri.</L>
<L>Simon to &thorn;at stede es went</L>
<L N="200">And saynt Peter was sethin efter sent.<NOTE PLACE="foot2">Das Reimwort lautet hall.</NOTE></L>
<L>When Petyr into &thorn;e hall come &thorn;an,</L>
<L>He said: "pese be vnto ilka man!"</L>
<L>Simon &thorn;an with hidose bere</L>
<L>Answerd him on &thorn;is manere:<NOTE PLACE="foot2">203 ff. Die 2. Col. ist deutlich.</NOTE><NOTE PLACE="foot2">157&mdash;204) I. Col. der R&uuml;ckseite, nur Versenden sind lesbar.</NOTE></L>
<L N="205">"Boy, of &thorn;i pese haue we no nede;</L>
<L>Ne it aw no man pese to bede<NOTE PLACE="foot2">Ne it falles no pese to bede.</NOTE></L>
<L>In place whore men er in debate;<NOTE PLACE="foot2">whare. at.</NOTE></L>
<L>And we er wroth, &thorn;at wele &thorn;ou wate,<NOTE PLACE="foot2">wrath.</NOTE></L>
<L>And pese omang us sal noght lend</L>
<L N="210">Till outhir of us be broght till end".<NOTE PLACE="foot2">ow&thorn;er. Die lat. Ueber|schrift fehlt.</NOTE></L>
</LG>
<Q>Disputatio Petri cum Simone.</Q>
<LG>
<L>
<PB REF="00000204.tif" N="66">Saynt Peter &thorn;an to Simon answerd:<NOTE PLACE="foot">(Peter fehlt). to him.</NOTE></L>
<L>"Whi ertow for pese so ferd?<NOTE PLACE="foot">ertou.</NOTE></L>
<L>Sen whore pese es, &thorn;ore es no sin,<NOTE PLACE="foot">whare. &thorn;are.</NOTE></L>
<L>Bot God es &thorn;ore omang man-kyn".<NOTE PLACE="foot">&thorn;are.</NOTE></L>
<L N="215">&THORN;an answerd Simon &thorn;us him till:<NOTE PLACE="foot">Simond.</NOTE></L>
<L>"&THORN;ou sais no-thing ogaynes my will:</L>
<L>For I am God and goddes sun,</L>
<L>And at mi will here wil I wun".<NOTE PLACE="foot">will. won.</NOTE></L>
<L>Saint Peter answerd wurdes hende:<NOTE PLACE="foot">&thorn;an said P. with wordes hende.</NOTE></L>
<L N="220">"Als fast &thorn;ou sall be fun a fende".</L>
<L>Saint Peter proued him be proces playne</L>
<L>And &thorn;e fende answerd fast ogayne;<NOTE PLACE="foot">221&mdash;2 fehlen.</NOTE></L>
<L>Bot euer he proued him wer &amp; wer,<NOTE PLACE="foot">And st. bot.</NOTE></L>
<L>To-tyme &thorn;e fende kouth say no ferr.<NOTE PLACE="foot">So &thorn;at st. to tyme. kowth. fer.</NOTE></L>
<L N="225">Ful lang strif was &thorn;am bitwene,<NOTE PLACE="foot">And st. ful.</NOTE></L>
<L>To Simon was ouercumen clene.<NOTE PLACE="foot">Til st. to. Simond.</NOTE></L>
<L>Saint Peter toke his bokes &thorn;are,</L>
<L>&THORN;at war made of &thorn;e fendes lare,</L>
<L>And kest &thorn;am fer into &thorn;e se,</L>
<L N="230">So &thorn;at &thorn;ai suld neuir funden be.<NOTE PLACE="foot">neuer.</NOTE></L>
<L>And all &thorn;e folk with precheing playn<NOTE PLACE="foot">preching plaine.</NOTE></L>
<L>Turned he &thorn;an vnto Crist ogayn.<NOTE PLACE="foot">&THORN;an fehlt. to st. vnto. ogaine.</NOTE></L>
<L>And Simon went oway in tene<NOTE PLACE="foot">Si|mond.</NOTE></L>
<L>To Rome, whore saint Peter had bene,<NOTE PLACE="foot">whare.</NOTE></L>
<L N="235">And &thorn;ore sune with his werkis ill<NOTE PLACE="foot">&thorn;are. sune fehlt. werkes.</NOTE></L>
<L>Turned mani to wirk hys will.<NOTE PLACE="foot">Turned he many folk him till.</NOTE></L>
<L>Nero was &thorn;an Emperour of Rome.</L>
<L>And vnto hym Simon come,<NOTE PLACE="foot">237&mdash;8) umgesetzt: And vnto Nero sone he come, &THORN;at &thorn;an was E. of R.</NOTE></L>
<L>He made him forto vnderstand<NOTE PLACE="foot">And st. he.</NOTE></L>
<L N="240">&THORN;at a lurdan was in his land,</L>
<L>A fals prechoure, &thorn;at Peter hight<NOTE PLACE="foot">prechore.</NOTE></L>
<L>And did him dere both day &amp; night.</L>
<L>&THORN;an gert he &thorn;e folk hym honoure<NOTE PLACE="foot">He made &thorn;e folk him to h.</NOTE></L>
<L>And sayd, he was &thorn;aire sauioure<NOTE PLACE="foot">sauiore.</NOTE></L>
<L N="245">And o&thorn;er god was none bot he;<NOTE PLACE="foot">nane.</NOTE></L>
<L>So trowed many of &thorn;at cete.<MILESTONE N="154" UNIT="folio"><NOTE PLACE="foot">in st. of.</NOTE></L>
<L>And &thorn;is ilk Emperoure Nero<NOTE PLACE="foot">ilk fehlt.</NOTE></L>
<L>Gaf ful grete credence him vnto.<NOTE PLACE="foot">ful fehlt. credens.</NOTE></L>
<L>When &thorn;is wurd to saint Peter come,<NOTE PLACE="foot">Sone &thorn;is worde.</NOTE></L>
<L N="250">He hied him hastili to Rome,<NOTE PLACE="foot">And hastily he went to R.</NOTE></L>
<L>&THORN;at fals eresi fast forto fell<NOTE PLACE="foot">eresy. fast fehlt.</NOTE></L>
<L>&THORN;at Simon made &thorn;e folk omell.<NOTE PLACE="foot">Simond.</NOTE></L>
<L>Saint Peter prechid fast him ogayn<NOTE PLACE="foot">Hier beginnt fol. 233.</NOTE><NOTE PLACE="foot">preched.</NOTE></L>
<L>And (bad) men suld &thorn;am for him sayn,<NOTE PLACE="foot">(And) bad for him men suld &thorn;am sain.</NOTE></L>
<L N="255">For he was fulfild of &thorn;e fende</L>
<L>And soght obout men sawls to schende.<NOTE PLACE="foot">man saul.</NOTE></L>
<L>&THORN;us als saint Peter prechid right,<NOTE PLACE="foot">saint fehlt.</NOTE></L>
<L>To him appered opon a night<NOTE PLACE="foot">apered.</NOTE></L>
<L>Ane angell &thorn;at fro heuyn was sent,<NOTE PLACE="foot">fra god.</NOTE></L>
<L N="260">And bad him tak with gude entent</L>
<L>For godes sake what men wold him do,<NOTE PLACE="foot">goddes. wald.</NOTE></L>
<L>And socure suld be sent him to.<NOTE PLACE="foot">socore.</NOTE></L>
<L>And on &thorn;e morn saint Paul was send,</L>
<L>With him in wathes forto wend.<NOTE PLACE="foot">wende.</NOTE></L>
<L N="265">Of his come was saynt Peter fayn.<NOTE PLACE="foot">faine.</NOTE></L>
<L>&THORN;an both &thorn;ai prechid Simon ogayn,<NOTE PLACE="foot">And st. &thorn;an. preched. Simond ogayne.</NOTE></L>
<L>&THORN;ai lerid &thorn;e folk of goddes lare<NOTE PLACE="foot">&THORN;ai preched fast. &THORN;e folk fehlt.</NOTE></L>
<L>And sone fordid all his fals fare,<NOTE PLACE="foot">sune.</NOTE></L>
<L>&THORN;ai made men leue with wurdes hende<NOTE PLACE="foot">And st. &thorn;ai. trow. wordes.</NOTE></L>
<L N="270">&THORN;at Simon Magus was a fende.<NOTE PLACE="foot">&THORN;at he was fulfild of &thorn;e f.</NOTE></L>
<L>Bot Nero and his men&yogh;e held</L>
<L>With Simon, for with &thorn;am he dweld:<NOTE PLACE="foot">Symond.</NOTE></L>
<L>He lerid &thorn;am euer of misbileue,</L>
<L>To bring &thorn;aire sawles vnto mischeue.<NOTE PLACE="foot">273&mdash;4) And held &thorn;am euer in mis|bileue Ogains o&thorn;er &thorn;at wald him greue.</NOTE></L>
<L N="275">&THORN;is Simon, als &thorn;e story vs says,<NOTE PLACE="foot">&thorn;an Simond. vs fehlt.</NOTE></L>
<L>Made his rofe &thorn;at he might rays<NOTE PLACE="foot">Rosed &thorn;at he myght rais</NOTE>
<PB REF="00000205.tif" N="67"></L>
<L>Ded men and gif life &thorn;am to.<NOTE PLACE="foot2">Ded men ogain &thorn;e life vnto.</NOTE></L>
<L>ssaynt Peter sayd he suld noght so.</L>
<L>And als &thorn;ai stude in &thorn;is debate,<NOTE PLACE="foot2">stode.</NOTE></L>
<L N="280">So was &thorn;ore broght furth in &thorn;e gate<NOTE PLACE="foot2">&thorn;are.</NOTE></L>
<L>A ded body, layd on a bere.<NOTE PLACE="foot2">layd fehlt. opon.</NOTE></L>
<L>And mekil folk drogh &thorn;eder nere,<NOTE PLACE="foot2">And all &thorn;e folk come &thorn;eder nere,</NOTE></L>
<L>Forto se &thorn;ore on what wise<NOTE PLACE="foot2">Forto se on any wise,</NOTE></L>
<L>Ou&thorn;er of &thorn;am suld ger him rise.<NOTE PLACE="foot2">If ow&thorn;er. might.</NOTE></L>
<L N="285">Nero &thorn;an and &thorn;e puple saise:<NOTE PLACE="foot2">&THORN;an Nero. sais.</NOTE></L>
<L>If one of &thorn;am &thorn;at cors mai raise<NOTE PLACE="foot2">Whe&thorn;er of &thorn;am so might him raise.</NOTE></L>
<L>And &thorn;at o&thorn;er may noght so,<NOTE PLACE="foot2">&thorn;e to&thorn;er might.</NOTE></L>
<L>To ded als sone men sal him do.<NOTE PLACE="foot2">Vnto ded men suld him do.</NOTE></L>
<L>Vnto &thorn;is both assentid &thorn;ai,<NOTE PLACE="foot2">And herto both assented &thorn;ai.</NOTE></L>
<L N="290">And Simon he suld fyrst assay.<NOTE PLACE="foot2">Symond.</NOTE></L>
<L>&THORN;an to &thorn;e body he made him boun</L>
<L>And sayd &thorn;ore his coniurisoun,<NOTE PLACE="foot2">made &thorn;are. coniorisoune.</NOTE></L>
<L>And did deuils craft so, or he leuyd,<NOTE PLACE="foot2">With deuils craft or euer he leuid,</NOTE></L>
<L>&THORN;at of &thorn;e ded cors moued &thorn;e heuyd.<NOTE PLACE="foot2">So &thorn;at &thorn;e ded man moued his h.</NOTE></L>
<L N="295">&THORN;an wald &thorn;e folk saint Pe(ter) war slayne.<NOTE PLACE="foot2">saint fehlt. haue slayn.</NOTE></L>
<L>He bad &thorn;am sese and said: "sertayne,<NOTE PLACE="foot2">sertain.</NOTE></L>
<L>&THORN;is fare es fals: &THORN;at proue I wele:<NOTE PLACE="foot1">Ms. I proue I.</NOTE></L>
<L>By deuils craft he dose ilk dele.<NOTE PLACE="foot2">297&mdash;8) fehlen. 300 sal. &thorn;e st. a.</NOTE></L>
<L>Makes &thorn;is wretche oway to wende,</L>
<L N="300">&THORN;an sall &yogh;e se it es a fende</L>
<L>&THORN;at moues &thorn;e heuid &thorn;us of &thorn;is man&mdash;<NOTE PLACE="foot2">&thorn;us fehlt.</NOTE></L>
<L>For life in him forsuth es nane".</L>
<L>&THORN;an gert &thorn;ai Symon gang oway:<NOTE PLACE="foot2">302 ff.) 2 Col., bis 330 lesbar, dann nur die Anf&auml;nge.</NOTE><NOTE PLACE="foot2">Simond.</NOTE></L>
<L>And still als stane &thorn;e bodi lay &mdash;</L>
<L N="305">&THORN;arof had Simon mekil schame.<NOTE PLACE="foot2">Simond.</NOTE></L>
<L>Saynt Peter spak in goddes name<NOTE PLACE="foot2">And Peter. Cristes.</NOTE></L>
<L>And said: "ded man, I cumand &thorn;e</L>
<L>In Jhesu name &thorn;at died on tre,</L>
<L>&THORN;at &thorn;ou rise up both hale &amp; fere<NOTE PLACE="foot2">both fehlt. and sounde</NOTE></L>
<L N="310">And tell what I will ask &thorn;e here.</L>
<L>Bot first &thorn;ou tell to more and les<NOTE PLACE="foot2">fehlen (so auch in Ash. 42).</NOTE></L>
<L>What maumet &thorn;at &thorn;is Simon es".<NOTE PLACE="foot2">And say vs what maumett es Simond.</NOTE></L>
<L>&THORN;e ded man rase &amp; tald bidene</L>
<L>Of him als he had herd and sene:<NOTE PLACE="foot2">What he of (heuin) and hell had sene (so auch Ash.).</NOTE></L>
<L N="315">He said: "&thorn;is Simon, suth to tell,<NOTE PLACE="foot2">Simond he said &thorn;e suth.</NOTE></L>
<L>Harls ful mony a sawl to hell.<NOTE PLACE="foot2">Harles many a saul.</NOTE></L>
<L>Trowes him noght! for ful es he</L>
<L>Of falshed and of fendes pouste;<NOTE PLACE="foot2">and &thorn;e, of fehlt.</NOTE></L>
<L>He schews yow meruails moni &amp; sere,<NOTE PLACE="foot2">schewes. yow fehlt. meruailes many.</NOTE></L>
<L N="320">And all es of &thorn;e fendes powere".</L>
<L>&THORN;an wald &thorn;e folk Simon haue slayn;<NOTE PLACE="foot2">haue Simond.</NOTE></L>
<L>Bot ssaint Peter spak &thorn;ar-ogayn,<NOTE PLACE="foot2">saint fehlt. fast spac. ogaine.</NOTE></L>
<L>He said: "it es oure lordes will<NOTE PLACE="foot2">And said if we do Cristes will,</NOTE></L>
<L>&THORN;at we do gude ogaynes ill &mdash;<NOTE PLACE="foot2">We sall do.</NOTE></L>
<L N="325">He bad vs do so all in-fere,<NOTE PLACE="foot2">al.</NOTE></L>
<L>Whils he welk omang us here;<NOTE PLACE="foot2">whill.</NOTE></L>
<L>And forto wreth hym war us lathe:<NOTE PLACE="foot2">lath.</NOTE></L>
<L>&THORN;arfore he sal haue here no skathe.<NOTE PLACE="foot2">&THORN;arfor we will do &thorn;is man no scath.</NOTE></L>
<L>Harm at &thorn;is tyme Inogh has he,</L>
<L N="330">When all folk may his falshed se".<NOTE PLACE="foot2">al.</NOTE></L>
<L>Bot herwithall &yogh;it leuid he noght,<NOTE PLACE="foot2">&thorn;arwithall.</NOTE></L>
