<L N="100">I warn &thorn;e wele &thorn;at I wil go</L>
<L>To him and pray par charite<NOTE PLACE="foot">Till.</NOTE></L>
<L>&THORN;at I may his disciple be."<NOTE PLACE="foot">desciple.</NOTE></L>
<L>Hermogines, when he &thorn;is herd,</L>
<L>Als a wude lion &thorn;an he ferd<NOTE PLACE="foot">Als a lyon for wode he ferd.</NOTE></L>
<L N="105">And to his steward sone he sayd:<NOTE PLACE="foot">And vnto Philete sone.</NOTE></L>
<L>"Ful dere &thorn;ou sal haby &thorn;is braid.<NOTE PLACE="foot">aby.</NOTE></L>
