<L N="160">(&THORN;o &thorn;ou) me gvnne greten<NOTE PLACE="foot">gun grete.</NOTE></L>
<L>(And nold) to sugen leten<NOTE PLACE="foot">And no day nold lete</NOTE></L>
<L>(Twies e)wche dayes.<NOTE PLACE="foot">Ac seidest fifti tviis.</NOTE></L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>(For &thorn;ou most say more</L>
<L>&THORN;ries fifti bi score,</L>
<L N="165">Al-so .I. teld &thorn;e.</L>
<L>To day a seveni&yogh;tte
<PB REF="00000361.tif" N="223"></L>
<L>.I.-clo&thorn;ed al ari&yogh;tte</L>
<L>&THORN;ou shalt me fair .I.-se.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Be here of al scille,<NOTE PLACE="foot1">l. stille?</NOTE></L>
<L N="170">And say wi&thorn; gode wille)<NOTE PLACE="foot">163&mdash;170, in D. fehlend, lauten in A.: For &thorn;ou most say more &THORN;riies fifti bi score, Al so y teld &thorn;e. To day a seuenni&yogh;t, Y-clo&thorn;ed al ari&yogh;t &THORN;ou schalt me fair y-se. &mdash; Be here of al scille And say wi&thorn; gode wille.</NOTE><NOTE PLACE="foot1">158&mdash;170 Im Ms. ist ein St&uuml;ck des Blattes schr&auml;g abgeschnitten. Das Fehlende ist aus Ms. Auch. erg&auml;nzt.</NOTE></L>
<L>Alle &thorn;e gretinges!<NOTE PLACE="foot2">Al &thorn;is greteinges.</NOTE></L>
<L>And .I. shal &thorn;e bringe<NOTE PLACE="foot2">y schal. bring.</NOTE></L>
<L>From mi sone, &thorn;e kinge,<NOTE PLACE="foot2">Fram. king.</NOTE></L>
<L>&THORN;anne gode tidinges."<NOTE PLACE="foot2">&thorn;anne fehlt.</NOTE></L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="175">Marie wente away.<NOTE PLACE="foot2">Mari went &thorn;o oway.</NOTE></L>
<L>And &thorn;e monk euche day<NOTE PLACE="foot2">monke ich.</NOTE></L>
<L>ffeyde ri&yogh;t &thorn;re si&thorn;es<NOTE PLACE="foot2">seyd.</NOTE></L>
<L>Mid wel gode wille<NOTE PLACE="foot2">wi&thorn;.</NOTE></L>
<L>Bo&thorn;e loude and stille</L>
<L N="180">&THORN;ese aue maries.<NOTE PLACE="foot2">His.</NOTE></L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>&THORN;at day a seveni&yogh;tte<NOTE PLACE="foot2">seuenni&yogh;t.</NOTE></L>
<L>Oure leuedi, foul of mi&yogh;tte,<NOTE PLACE="foot2">Our. ful. mi&yogh;t.</NOTE></L>
<L>To &thorn;at moneke com,<NOTE PLACE="foot2">&thorn;e monk. cam.</NOTE></L>
<L>.I.-clo&thorn;ed swi&thorn;e bri&yogh;tte</L>
<L N="185">In &thorn;at wede alri&yogh;tte,<NOTE PLACE="foot2">184&mdash;5) In hir wede ri&yogh;t Y-clo&thorn;ed swi&thorn;e bri&yogh;t.</NOTE></L>
<L>And &thorn;onkede &thorn;at mon.<NOTE PLACE="foot2">&thorn;onked &thorn;e man.</NOTE></L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>"Fair is, lo, mi wede,<NOTE PLACE="foot2">now st. lo.</NOTE></L>
<L>For bedes &thorn;at &thorn;ou bede,<NOTE PLACE="foot1">Ms. q&macr;met.</NOTE></L>
<L>And &thorn;ou hauest quemet me.<NOTE PLACE="foot2">&THORN;atow hast &yogh;eue me.</NOTE></L>
<L N="190">Mi sone &thorn;e wille rede,<NOTE PLACE="foot2">wil.</NOTE></L>
<L>&THORN;at no&thorn;ing &thorn;e nadrede &mdash;<NOTE PLACE="foot2">&thorn;at &thorn;ou no &thorn;ing no drede.</NOTE></L>
<L>Here ich hit telle &thorn;e.<NOTE PLACE="foot2">For-so&thorn;e y telle &thorn;e.</NOTE></L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Vuene &thorn;ou art home .I. come,<NOTE PLACE="foot2">When. hom y-nome.</NOTE></L>
<L>&THORN;ou shalt Abbot bicome,<NOTE PLACE="foot2">193&mdash;4) umgesetzt.</NOTE><NOTE PLACE="foot2">abot.</NOTE></L>
<L N="195">For &thorn;in Abbot shal deye.<NOTE PLACE="foot2">your. schal dye.</NOTE></L>
<L>Haue euere in &thorn;i wone<NOTE PLACE="foot2">Haue &thorn;ou euer in wone</NOTE></L>
<L>To suggen bi coustome<NOTE PLACE="foot1">Ms. mi st. bi.</NOTE><NOTE PLACE="foot2">To sigge bi costome.</NOTE></L>
<L>&THORN;ine aues euche daye!<NOTE PLACE="foot2">ich day.</NOTE></L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Wend ouer-al aboute<NOTE PLACE="foot2">Wende al about.</NOTE></L>
<L N="200">And preche inne and oute<NOTE PLACE="foot2">preche it in. out.</NOTE></L>
<L>(&THORN;at) &thorn;is is mi sauter!</L>
<L>"(For al) &thorn;at euche daye<NOTE PLACE="foot2">ich day.</NOTE></L>
<L>(Wille &thorn;is) for me saye,<NOTE PLACE="foot1">201&mdash;3. Im Ms. ist ein St&uuml;ck des Blattes schr&auml;g abgeschnitten. Das Fehlende ist aus Ms. Auch. erg&auml;nzt.</NOTE><NOTE PLACE="foot2">wil. for my fay.</NOTE></L>
<L>.I. shal hem ben welner.<MILESTONE N="132" UNIT="folio"></L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="205">Monek, ich telle hit &thorn;e<NOTE PLACE="foot2">Leue monke ich telle &thorn;e.</NOTE></L>
<L>&THORN;at &thorn;ou most al for me</L>
<L>Wenden wide-wore<NOTE PLACE="foot2">ner and wide.</NOTE></L>
<L>And telle &thorn;is tidinge<NOTE PLACE="foot2">And tellen of &thorn;is &thorn;ing.</NOTE></L>
