<L>On &thorn;e worste abouen er&thorn;e.<NOTE PLACE="foot2">A On of &thorn;e, B And &thorn;e. AB werst. A aboue, B abouyne. B erth.</NOTE><NOTE PLACE="foot2">Nach 366 hat B: The lechor wenes &thorn;at lyue non is So mery as hys awne is.</NOTE><NOTE PLACE="foot">365&mdash;6) fehlen in T.</NOTE><NOTE PLACE="foot2">A commene womane, I the tell, May soullys drawyne to hell (diese 2 V. fehlen in B). In holy wrytte (B wryte) hit is sette That (fehlt in B) lechory ys &thorn;e fendys nette. Hierauf folgt (vgl. Vernon): Gloteny (B glotony) I schall discryue (B deserne) Amonge manekynd it yse (B is) foll (B full) ryue (B &yogh;erne); &THORN;erfore (B Thereof) &thorn;e fende (B fend) takyne (B takys) bale Whenne (B when) mene bene (B be) dronkyn (B dronke) of wyne &amp; (B or) alle (B ale); They cryene &amp; sweryne (B The suere &thorn;an) as they were wode, Be Crystis herte (B passyone) and be hys blode, And vp-braydyne (B vp-brayd) hyme of his passyone; Therefore &thorn;ey schall (fehlt in B) haue hys malysoune, But (B bot) &thorn;ey (fehlt in T) scryue (B schryue) hym (B &thorn;em) of (&thorn;er, f. in T) glotony, In hell schall be &thorn;er baly (dieser V. fehlt in T). &mdash; (Die folg. 6 Verse des Ms. Vern. fehlen). &mdash;</NOTE></L>
