<L N="510">And both wer dampned to helle.<NOTE PLACE="foot2">509&mdash;10) fehlen in B.</NOTE><NOTE PLACE="foot2">T And weron Idampnyd. A And seth he was. T into.</NOTE></L>
<L>The &thorn;rydde reson, y &thorn;e telle:<NOTE PLACE="foot2">A &thorn;irde, B thyrd, T &thorn;erd. A I schall &thorn;e, T I wyll &thorn;e. B wote &yogh;e wele.</NOTE></L>
<L>vpon a fryday Caym slow&yogh; Abelle,<NOTE PLACE="foot2">ABT On. A Keyme, B Cayme, T Cayne. A sclewe, BT slew.</NOTE></L>
<L>The fyrste martyr for sothe aply&yogh;t<NOTE PLACE="foot2">AT first. T marter. A he was st. forsothe. T I ply&yogh;t.</NOTE></L>
<L>That was martered for god almy&yogh;t;<NOTE PLACE="foot2">T That euer. T marterid, A sclawe.</NOTE></L>
<L N="515">And Cayme for &thorn;at same &thorn;yng<NOTE PLACE="foot2">A Keyme, T Ceyme. A &thorn;at ilke, T that wyckid. A &THORN;ynge.</NOTE></L>
<L>hadde &thorn;e curse of our heuene kyng.<NOTE PLACE="foot1">515&mdash;6 fehlen in Vern.</NOTE><NOTE PLACE="foot2">513&mdash;16) fehlen in B.</NOTE><NOTE PLACE="foot2">AT had. A cors, T corse. A kynge.</NOTE></L>
<L>The fowrthe reson ys full swete:<NOTE PLACE="foot2">A ferth, B forte, T fowreth. B resone, suete.</NOTE></L>
<L>how Gabryell our lady dede grete;<NOTE PLACE="foot2">A &thorn;at, T When. A gan oure lady, T Mari gan. dede fehlt in B. AT gret.</NOTE></L>
<L>vpon a fryday wyth mylde mode<NOTE PLACE="foot2">ABT On. ABT myld. T mod.</NOTE></L>
<L N="520">Goddes sone toke flesh &amp; blode<NOTE PLACE="foot2">A god sone, B Jhesu. AB both flesch. T blod.</NOTE></L>
<L>Of &thorn;at swete mayde Marie<NOTE PLACE="foot2">A Of &thorn;e mayd myld Marye, T All of the maydyn M.</NOTE></L>
<L>wythowten wemme of her body.<NOTE PLACE="foot1">521&mdash;2 fehlen in Vern.</NOTE><NOTE PLACE="foot2">521&mdash;22) fehlen in B.</NOTE><NOTE PLACE="foot2">A With weme (!). T wem. A here.</NOTE></L>
<L>The fyfte reson I telle beforn:<NOTE PLACE="foot2">B fyft. A as it telles byforne. BT I tell &thorn;e b.</NOTE></L>
<L>vpon a fryday Jhesus was born<NOTE PLACE="foot2">AT On. T Jhesu, A god sone. B Jhesus was of Mary borne.</NOTE></L>
<L N="525">Of &thorn;at swete holy vyrgyne,<NOTE PLACE="foot2">A Of &thorn;e mayde Mary &thorn;e holy virgyne, T Of the holy wyrgene.</NOTE></L>
<L>To borow our sowles out of pyne.<NOTE PLACE="foot2">525&mdash;26) fehlen in B.</NOTE><NOTE PLACE="foot2">A To by man soul frome hell pyne, T To bryng oure soulis fro hell p.</NOTE></L>
<L>The syxte reson ys of hy&yogh; empryse:<NOTE PLACE="foot2">A sext, B sexte. AT is faire emprise (T epreise), B is gode praysed.</NOTE></L>
<L>when Jhesus toke hys cyrcumcise,<NOTE PLACE="foot2">ABT &thorn;at Jhesu Cryst was c. B conseyued.</NOTE></L>
<L>vpon a fryday blode gan he blede,<NOTE PLACE="foot2">A Opon a f. Cryst gan blede.</NOTE></L>
<L N="530">For &thorn;e gylt of our mysdede</L>
<L>And for &thorn;e synne of Adam &amp; Eue</L>
<L>That blode he bledde for our beleue.<NOTE PLACE="foot1">529&mdash;32 fehlen in Vern.</NOTE><NOTE PLACE="foot2">A His blod was sched.</NOTE></L>
<L>The seuen&thorn;e reson, tell y kan:<NOTE PLACE="foot2">529&mdash;33) fehlen in BT.</NOTE><NOTE PLACE="foot2">A souen, B seuent. BT canne.</NOTE></L>
<L>how seynt Steuen, goddes man,<NOTE PLACE="foot2">533&mdash;4) in T umgestellt.</NOTE><NOTE PLACE="foot2">ABT &thorn;at st. how. T sent Stewyne, B seynte Stephyne &thorn;e holy mane. AT godys.</NOTE></L>
<L N="535">vpon a fryday was stoned to dede<NOTE PLACE="foot2">ABT On. B stonyd, T stenyde, A do. T to &thorn;e dethe. B ded.</NOTE></L>
<L>Thorow Herode &amp; hys fals rede.<NOTE PLACE="foot2">A &thorn;orough, B Throw, T Thorowe. Herode fehlt in A. B Herod.</NOTE></L>
<L>The VIII reson y kan telle,<NOTE PLACE="foot2">ABT resone. A I schall &yogh;ow, B I wyll &yogh;ou, T I wyll.</NOTE></L>
<L>&yogh;ef &yogh;e wyll a stounde dwelle:<NOTE PLACE="foot2">B Iff &thorn;at, T &yogh;yf &thorn;at, A And. A woll. B stound.</NOTE></L>
<L>vpon a fryday saynt Jon &thorn;e baptyst<NOTE PLACE="foot2">AT On. T frayday. T sent, baptest.</NOTE></L>
<L N="540">was martered for &thorn;e loue of Cryst<NOTE PLACE="foot2">A Imartird, T martyred. T for Jhesu Criste.</NOTE></L>
<L>In harueste aftur &thorn;e assumpcyon &mdash;<NOTE PLACE="foot2">A In &thorn;e. A heruest, T herueste. AT aftyr.</NOTE></L>
<L>hys day ys called decollacyoune.<NOTE PLACE="foot2">539&mdash;542) fehlen in B.</NOTE><NOTE PLACE="foot2">A &thorn;at is Iclepyd &thorn;e decollacion.</NOTE></L>
<L>The IX reson ys full gode:<NOTE PLACE="foot2">T good.</NOTE></L>
<L>That goddes sone dyed on &thorn;e Rode<NOTE PLACE="foot2">AT god st. goddes sone, B Jhesu. T deyed. T vpone, rood.</NOTE></L>
<L N="545">vpon a fryday, as y &yogh;ou telle,<NOTE PLACE="foot2">AT On. T frayday.</NOTE></L>
<L>To bye our sowles out of helle.<NOTE PLACE="foot2">545&mdash;46) fehlen in B.</NOTE><NOTE PLACE="foot2">A He bou&yogh;t man soul. T To byue (!). T fro.</NOTE></L>
<L>Thys ys &thorn;e ten&thorn;e reson:</L>
<L>Of our ladyes assumpcioune:<NOTE PLACE="foot2">547&mdash;48) B: On &thorn;e frydey was our lady Assumpsyone, That is callyd &thorn;e X resone.</NOTE><NOTE PLACE="foot2">AT lady. T the ass.</NOTE>
<PB REF="00000663.tif" N="525"></L>
<L>On a frydaye she &yogh;olde &thorn;e gost<NOTE PLACE="foot">A scho &yogh;eld, T sche &yogh;eldyd. T goste.</NOTE></L>
<L N="550">To her sone &thorn;at she loued most;<NOTE PLACE="foot">T Thyll. A here, T hir. T sonne. T scho, T sch&umacr; (!) T lovyd.</NOTE><NOTE PLACE="foot">Nach 550) hat A (u. V): And now in heuen &thorn;at virgyn is With body &amp; soul forsoth Iwis.</NOTE></L>
<L>Ther he ys kyng, she ys qwene &mdash;<NOTE PLACE="foot">A Crist st he. A kenge. A scho, T ther he. T quene.</NOTE></L>
<L>I-blessed mot &thorn;at tyme bene!<NOTE PLACE="foot">549&mdash;552) fehlen in B.</NOTE><NOTE PLACE="foot">A Iblyssyd, T Iblessid. T bee.</NOTE></L>
<L>The XI reson ys full trewe:</L>
<L>That &thorn;e apostell saynt Andrewe<NOTE PLACE="foot">AT apostyll. A seint, T sent.</NOTE></L>
<L N="555">vpon a fryday was don on crosse;<NOTE PLACE="foot">AT On. A he was. A cros, T crose.</NOTE></L>
<L>To god he called wyth meke voys<NOTE PLACE="foot">T calid, A clepyd. AT myld. A vos, T woyce.</NOTE></L>
<L>And sayde: fadur yn trynyte,<NOTE PLACE="foot">Statt 553&mdash;7) hat B: The XI off seynte Andrew &thorn;at holy mane How he sufferd hys martyrdome.</NOTE><NOTE PLACE="foot">A And he. T sayde to god. T trenyte.</NOTE></L>
<L>Thys suffre y for &thorn;e loue of &thorn;e.<NOTE PLACE="foot">AT &thorn;is passione I suffre (T suffyr) for &thorn;e.</NOTE></L>
<L>The XII reson: wyth mylde mode<NOTE PLACE="foot">AB myld.</NOTE></L>
<L N="560">Seynt Elene fonde &thorn;e holy Rode<NOTE PLACE="foot">AT &thorn;at seynt (T sente), B How s. ABT Elyne. B fond, A fand. holy fehlt in BT.</NOTE></L>
<L>vpon &thorn;e mounte of Caluarye &mdash;<NOTE PLACE="foot">A On a fryday atte. T On &thorn;e monte. AT Caluerye.</NOTE></L>
<L>On &thorn;at Rode Jhesus gan dye,<NOTE PLACE="foot">T And one the rood, A On whiche rode. A god, E Jhesu. T con, A gan on.</NOTE><NOTE PLACE="foot">Nach 562 haben AT (u. V): &THORN;ere was &thorn;e holy cros Ifounde (T: One a fryday the crose was fowynd), &thorn;ei doluyn it oute of &thorn;e grounde (T That deepe was doluyne ovndyr &thorn;e grond).</NOTE></L>
<L>And was born to &thorn;at cyte<NOTE PLACE="foot">A &amp; bare it to Jeru|salem &thorn;at rych cite. T And was brow&yogh;t to &thorn;e c.</NOTE></L>
<L>Wyth Joye &amp; grete solempnite.<NOTE PLACE="foot">561&mdash;64) fehlen in B.</NOTE><NOTE PLACE="foot">A With gret ioy and s. T grette solempnyty. &mdash;</NOTE></L>
<L N="565">The XIII reson ys verament:<NOTE PLACE="foot">Nach 565 hat A noch folg. Verse, die in T nach 568 folgen: &THORN;e XIII (T XIIII) reson, I schall &yogh;ow telle (T tell &yogh;oue), And &yogh;e wolleth a stound dwelle (T &yogh;yff ye will listyne nowe): Seynt Petire (T &yogh;one sent Petyr), &thorn;at holy (fehlen in T) pope of Rome, An holy man &amp; a wyse of dome (dieser V. f. in T), On (T Vpone) a fryday he (f. in T) was done (T was dede) on rode, &thorn;e hed (T His heede) dounward, &thorn;e (T his) fet vpe stode. &THORN;e Jewys hong hym (T hyme hangyd) on &thorn;e rode-tre, On a (T the) fryday, &thorn;us endyd he. &THORN;e fourten (T XV) resone I schall (T will) tell &yogh;ow (T youe tell), And &yogh;e to me wolleth lystyne now (T &YOGH;yf ye wyll a whylee here dwell). Seynt (T Of sent), Poul (T Powle) &thorn;at (T the) holy man, On (T Wpone) a fryday (T frayday) he was sclayn (T slayne). &THORN;ei smot of his heued with a swerde (T Hys heed was smettyne of with a sverde), And &thorn;us with s. Poul &thorn;ei ferde (T Thus-gatys was sent Poule aferde). Petyr &amp; Poul godys discipils were &thorn;ei, Bothe were &thorn;ei martird (T slayne) on (T vpone) a day. &mdash;</NOTE><NOTE PLACE="foot">A &thorn;e XV. is fehlt in ABT. T weramente.</NOTE></L>
<L>That god shall sytte yn Jugement<NOTE PLACE="foot">AT &yogh;eue &thorn;e. B That god on ester-dey schall gyff j.</NOTE></L>
<L>vpon a fryday wyth mylde mode,<NOTE PLACE="foot">ABT On B &thorn;e. AB drery, T dreury st. mylde.</NOTE></L>
<L>wyth feet &amp; hondes &amp; sydes all blode.<NOTE PLACE="foot">T fette, &amp; vor hondys fehlt. A hondes &amp; fet. B Oure lord bou&yogh;t vs with hys blode.</NOTE></L>
<L>Man, haue &thorn;ou fryday yn mynde<NOTE PLACE="foot">A &thorn;erefor man. BT &thorn;ou haue, &thorn;ou fehlt in A. BT mynd.</NOTE></L>
<L N="570">For &thorn;ese resones &thorn;at y fynde!<NOTE PLACE="foot">A thys XV, B &thorn;is, T thes. AB resons, T resonys. A wryt, B wrytene st. &thorn;at. B fynd.</NOTE></L>
<L>For &thorn;e fryday ys a day of chaunce<NOTE PLACE="foot">For &thorn;e fehlt in AT.</NOTE></L>
<L>Best to faste &amp; to do penaunce.<NOTE PLACE="foot">571&mdash;2) fehlen in B.</NOTE><NOTE PLACE="foot">T Beste. A fast. AT to fehlt.</NOTE></L>
<L>The satyrday aftur, sykurly,<NOTE PLACE="foot">AT wyterly, B sertenly.</NOTE></L>
<L>Is beste for to faste for our lady;<NOTE PLACE="foot">ABT gode to. A fast. A for &thorn;e loue of oure lady.</NOTE></L>
<L N="575">Thorow her we bene of bale vnbonde<NOTE PLACE="foot">T Thow we. A ere, T were. A balys. T bounde.</NOTE></L>
<L>And brow&yogh;t out of helle grounde;<NOTE PLACE="foot">of fehlt in T. T grownd.</NOTE></L>
<L>She ys called welle of mercy<NOTE PLACE="foot">A scho; clepyd &thorn;e.</NOTE></L>
<L>To alle &thorn;at wyll to her cry,<NOTE PLACE="foot">A wolleth. T vpone. A here.</NOTE></L>
<L>To wash &amp; to make clene<NOTE PLACE="foot">A Forto. T To helpene.</NOTE></L>
<L N="580">All &thorn;o &thorn;at yn synne bene;<NOTE PLACE="foot">&thorn;o fehlt in AT. A &thorn;at euer.</NOTE></L>
<L>The see-sterre called she ys,<NOTE PLACE="foot">A day-stere, T lode-ster. A clepyd scho. T schall schewe vs.</NOTE>
<PB REF="00000664.tif" N="526"></L>
<L>The ry&yogh;th way vs to wys;<NOTE PLACE="foot">T waye to hewyne bles.</NOTE></L>
<L>Of her sprong &thorn;at swete flour,<NOTE PLACE="foot">AT here. A swet, T swette.</NOTE></L>
<L>Jhesus Cryste, our sauyour &mdash;<NOTE PLACE="foot">A Cryst. A oure, T owyr.</NOTE></L>
<L N="585">I-blessed mote &thorn;ey all be<NOTE PLACE="foot">I fehlt in T. AT mot. AT alle.</NOTE></L>
<L>That seruen Marye mayden fre!"<NOTE PLACE="foot">A seruyth AT &thorn;at mayd (T maydene) with hert (T herte) fre. &mdash;</NOTE><NOTE PLACE="foot">Nach 586) hat A jetzt (vgl. v. 413&mdash;426): &THORN;e Emperoure seyd: by seynt Symeone, &thorn;ow hast schewyd me a faire resone. Bot telle, child, if &thorn;ou can, What &thorn;yng wrathes most god &amp; man? &THORN;e child sayde: dedys thre, I schall &thorn;e telle which &thorn;ei be. &THORN;e first is ded of fame, If a man dey in wykyd schame. &THORN;e to&thorn;ere is pride in body here, &thorn;at is so stronge and no (!) stere, &thorn;at gretly noyes mans body with-ine, Or &thorn;e lyf and soul may part atwyne. &THORN;e &thorn;irde is, as sayth &thorn;e clerkys, If a man haue no part in gode werkes. &mdash;</NOTE></L>
<L>The emperour wyth wordes sterne<NOTE PLACE="foot">A &thorn;e e. sayd. AT wordys. A steryne, T sturne.</NOTE></L>
<L>To &thorn;at chylde he sayde &yogh;erne:<NOTE PLACE="foot">T &thorn;e. A &thorn;an vnto &thorn;e child full &yogh;erne.</NOTE><NOTE PLACE="foot">575&mdash;588) fehlen in B.</NOTE></L>
<L>"Chylde, he sayde, I coniure &thorn;e<NOTE PLACE="foot">he sayde fehlt in T. T comaund. B: The emperour seyd, I coniure the.</NOTE></L>
<L N="590">In &thorn;e name of &thorn;e trynyte<NOTE PLACE="foot">T trynete.</NOTE></L>
<L>And of &thorn;e passyon of Jhesus Cryst<NOTE PLACE="foot">A &thorn;orough. T &amp; in &thorn;e name of &thorn;e passyone of Cryst.</NOTE></L>
<L>And of hys deth &amp; hys vpryst:<NOTE PLACE="foot">And fehlt in B. T in st. of. T dethe. A &amp; of his. BT vpryste.</NOTE></L>
<L>That &thorn;ou me &thorn;e so&thorn;e say,<NOTE PLACE="foot">T &thorn;at &thorn;owe me tell &amp; sothe to saye. B soth.</NOTE></L>
<L>Ere &thorn;ou fro me wende away:<NOTE PLACE="foot">A Or, B or &thorn;at. T er that. B wend fro me, T wende hens, A here wende.</NOTE></L>
<L N="595">Whe&thorn;ur &thorn;ou be wykked angell or good?"<NOTE PLACE="foot">A Whedere art &thorn;ou a. ABT wykyd. A o&thorn;er a. AB gode.</NOTE></L>
<L>The chyld answered wyth mylde mood:<NOTE PLACE="foot">ABT myld mode.</NOTE></L>
<L>"I am he &thorn;at &thorn;e wro&yogh;th<NOTE PLACE="foot">he fehlt in B. B hath wrou&yogh;t; T bowght.</NOTE></L>
<L>And on &thorn;e Rode &thorn;e dere bow&yogh;th."<NOTE PLACE="foot">A And with my blod full dere &thorn;e b. &thorn;e fehlt in BT. B haue bou&yogh;t, T hathe bou&yogh;t.</NOTE></L>
<L>The chylde styed yn-to heuen &thorn;o,<NOTE PLACE="foot">AB went, T styght. ABT to.</NOTE></L>
<L N="600">In-to &thorn;e place &thorn;at he come fro.<NOTE PLACE="foot">B Vnto, AT To. A &thorn;at place, BT &thorn;e blys.</NOTE></L>
<L>The emperour kneled down to &thorn;e grounde<NOTE PLACE="foot">A &thorn;en knelyd. down fehlt in AB. B on. &thorn;e fehlt in A. T grond.</NOTE></L>
<L>And &thorn;anked god &thorn;at same stounde,<NOTE PLACE="foot">BT &thorn;ankyd. AB blissed, T swette. T stound.</NOTE><NOTE PLACE="foot">Nach 602 hat T: And thankyd god of hys swete grace, That he there saw his swette face.</NOTE></L>
<L>And bycam a good man, as we rede,<NOTE PLACE="foot">A And he. ABT become. a fehlt in T. AB gode, T crystyne. T red.</NOTE></L>
<L>In bedes byddyng &amp; almesse-dede,<NOTE PLACE="foot">T In bedys, byddyng fehlt; A In body and &thorn;ought &amp;, B In prayere. BT &amp; in. AB almus, T allmys.</NOTE></L>
<L N="605">And serued god yn all wyse,<NOTE PLACE="foot">T serwy(d). A And prayed to god in alle &thorn;is wyse.</NOTE></L>
<L>And kam to heuene for hys seruyse.<NOTE PLACE="foot">A And leued and died in his seruyse. T: And here endyth Epotyse (Schluss).</NOTE><NOTE PLACE="foot">Nach 606 hat AB noch den Schluss des Ms. Vernon: Seynt Johne &thorn;e vangelyst, &thorn;at went (B was) in erth with Jhesu Cryst, This taille (B tale) he wrote in latyne In holy wryt (B wryte) in (B &amp; in) parchemyne, And (B He) bad and (fehlen in B) comand (B commandyd) alle mankynde This ensample (B The passyone of Cryst) to haue in mynde. A schliesst: &THORN;us endyth &thorn;is talkyng, God graunt vs alle gode endynge, Amen, Amen say we now alle, &thorn;at it mot so byfalle. Her endith Ypotys. B schliesst: Amen, amen fore charyte, God grante vs &thorn;at it so be. Here endys &thorn;is talkyng, God grante vs all hys blyssyng. &mdash;</NOTE></L>
<L>God &yogh;eue grace yt so mote be,</L>
<L>Sayth all amen for charyte!<NOTE PLACE="foot">605-8) fehlen in B.</NOTE></L>
</LG>
