<DIV1 TYPE="Middle English poem quoted in notes (included)"><PB REF="00000666.tif" N="528">

<PB REF="00000667.tif" N="529">
<HEAD>Lamentacio peccatoris (Ms. Thornton fol. 51 b).</HEAD>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>"All crystyn men &thorn;at wawkys me bye,</L>
<L>Behold &amp; see &thorn;is dulful seyght!</L>
<L>I beyd nother to kawl nor to crye,</L>
<L>I am so dampyd a woful weyght.</L>
<L N="5">Tayk heyd of me, both kyng &amp; kneyt,</L>
<L>&amp; mend yow heyr, qwyllys &yogh;e haue space;</L>
<L>Fore, qwen &yogh;e haue lost euer-lastyng leght,</L>
<L>Fro mercy be gone, &yogh;e gayt no grace.</L>
<L>Qwen I was &yogh;owyng, os now er &yogh;e,</L>
<L N="10">&THORN;an beyd I neuer a fayrere lyfe,</L>
<L>I spent my &yogh;erys in vanite,</L>
<L>In vane-glory &amp; in stryfe.</L>
<L>I had no hape, qwyllys I was heyre,</L>
<L>To ryes &amp; me repent;</L>
<L N="15">Now am I broght apon a beyre,</L>
<L>Itt ys to lett, for I am schentt.</L>
<L>Gret othes to me &thorn;<SUP>a</SUP> war ful ryfe,</L>
<L>I had no grace for to amend;</L>
<L>I sparyd neuer noder madyn ne wyfe,</L>
<L N="20">&amp; &thorn;at hase browght me to &thorn;is end.</L>
<L>In lecheri I led my lyfe,</L>
<L>Qwen I had god &amp; gud (!) at wyll;</L>
<L>I slew my-self with-owt a knyfe;</L>
<L>In glotony I toyk my fyll;</L>
<L N="25">In sclewyth I lay &amp; sclepyd styll,</L>
<L>I was desauyd throw a tryst.</L>
<L>&THORN;is dredful ded I druwe me tyll,</L>
<L>And all ys tornyd to "adywyst".</L>
<L>Had y wyst, yt wyll not bee,</L>
<L N="30">I wot I mune neuer more thweyn.
<PB REF="00000668.tif" N="530"></L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Fore hym &thorn;at dyed for &yogh;ow &amp; me,<NOTE PLACE="foot">Dieser Vers im Ms. doppelt.</NOTE></L>
<L>Ryes, &amp; rest not in &yogh;owr synn!</L>
<L>Qwen I was lapyd in synnys seyre &mdash;</L>
<L N="35">Sore to yow I mayk my mone &mdash;</L>
<L>&THORN;er meght me help no gud prayer,</L>
<L>I had no god bot gud alone.</L>
<L>Qwen I was &yogh;owng &amp; in my flowres,</L>
<L>I was as blythe as byrd on breyr:</L>
<L N="40">&THORN;at garrys me suffer &thorn;es scherp schoris</L>
<L>And by &thorn;is bargan wonder deyre.</L>
<L>Woo to &thorn;es, wer-euer &thorn;<SUP>a</SUP> bee,</L>
<L>That hase &thorn;er V inwyttys to wyll,</L>
<L>&THORN;at wyl not now tayk tent to me</L>
<L N="45">&amp; knawe &thorn;e gud byfor &thorn;e yll.</L>
<L>Pure for fawt <I>&yogh;e</I> lat not spyll &mdash;</L>
<L>For, &amp; <I>&yogh;e</I> do, &yogh;owr ded ys deght;</L>
<L>The lust of &yogh;owr fleych wyl neuer fulfyll,</L>
<L>By war in luscefer not at <I>&yogh;e</I> lyght.</L>
<L N="50">In deligat metys I had gret delytt,</L>
<L>So had I wyne on-to my pay:</L>
<L>&THORN;at garrys &thorn;es wormys on me to byt,</L>
<L>And euer &thorn;er sang ys wyllossay (!).<NOTE PLACE="foot">Ms. &thorn;er st. my.</NOTE></L>
<L>I meght not fast, nor I wold not pray,</L>
<L N="55">I thoyt to a mendyd in my egge;</L>
<L>I draue euer of fro day to day &mdash;</L>
<L>And now am I lokyd in a kage.</L>
<L>The kage yt be on byrnyng fyere,</L>
<L>&THORN;at I am ordand in to dwell;</L>
<L N="60">Thys haue &thorn;<SUP>a</SUP> gyuyn me to my hyere,</L>
<L>Euer to last in &thorn;e panys of hell.</L>
<L>Thus am I feterd with fendys so fell,<NOTE PLACE="foot">Unten auf der Seite steht: Johannes.</NOTE></L>
<L>as qwo bynd besse in-to a stall.</L>
<L>&THORN;er ys no tong my woo kan tell &mdash;</L>
<L N="65">By war, gud serys, of syche a fall!</L>
<L>Gentyll brother, haue in mynd</L>
<L>hyen qwen &thorn;ou schall weynd away;</L>
<L>To &thorn;i awyn (&thorn;ou) sall be neuer on-kynd.</L>
<L>Remenber &thorn;at bothe nyght &amp; day!</L>
<L N="70">Full derly to hyme &thorn;at &yogh;e pray,</L>
<L>To hym &thorn;at was don apon a tre,</L>
<L>To safe &yogh;owr sallis on dowymysday,</L>
<L>Qwen all sallys sauyd mon be.</L>
<L>Than may &thorn;er na luyd men for &yogh;ow mute,</L>
<L N="75">No iustys nor no man of lawe;</L>
<L>Fore, &amp; &thorn;<SUP>a</SUP> (do) &mdash; &thorn;<SUP>a</SUP> be no buyt,</L>
<L>&THORN;er charter wyll not preyf worthe a hawe.</L>
<L>Thus euery man, &yogh;e tayk gud tent,</L>
<L>Euery man in hys degre.</L>
<L N="80">Me thynk I heyr a horn blowe.</L>
<L>All crystyn men, be war by me!"</L>
<TRAILER>Explicit lamentacio.</TRAILER>
</LG>
